  "takeaways": [
    "The split architecture defines a deposit-proximate core treatment separately from the mixed TOC/ROW support bundle instead of forcing one headline treatment object to do both jobs.",
    "The quarterly split is mechanically exact in the panel: max TDC decomposition gap \u2248 4.26e-14, max residual decomposition gap \u2248 1.14e-13.",
    "At h0, baseline residual \u2248 -72.74, core residual \u2248 -5.51, so the split support bundle carries about 65.40 of treatment-side movement.",
    "At h0, the deposit-proximate core treatment response is still sizable (\u2248 63.10), which is why the split should be treated as an interpretation redesign rather than a zeroing-out exercise.",
    "Path evidence stays mixed inside the support bundle: quarter by quarter the preferred path is `direct_deposit_path_dominant`, but at h0 the preferred path is `broad_support_path_dominant`.",
    "This split directly implements the repo-level redesign recommendation: `split_core_plus_support_bundle`."
  ]
}
